Laikipia governor hopeful Nderitu Muriithi yesterday received a boost after three aspirants stepped down from the race and promised to back him.Thuita Mwangi, James Mathenge and James Mwangi, who were running as independents, made the announcement yesterday at Central Park in Nanyuki town. Muriithi is vying as an independent. He will faceoff with Jubilee nominee and incumbent Governor Joshua Irungu.The deal for the three to abandon the race was brokered by Simon Mithamo who contested for the Jubilee senator ticket, but lost to John Kinyua.